# NeonCore 5G — Wireshark name-resolution hosts file
#
# Standard /etc/hosts format (IP<whitespace>name). Load in Wireshark via
# Preferences > Name Resolution > "Hosts file" (or drop it in your Wireshark
# personal config folder as a file literally named "hosts" and enable
# "Resolve network (IP) addresses"). Pod IPs change on every pod
# restart/recreation -- regenerate this whenever that happens.
#
# Regenerate with:
#   kubectl -n neoncore get pods -o custom-columns='NAME:.metadata.name,IP:.status.podIP' --no-headers
#   kubectl -n monitoring get pods -o custom-columns='NAME:.metadata.name,IP:.status.podIP' --no-headers

